1
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:41,500
<i> Jessica! Hazel!</i>

2
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:43,433
<i>- Mister!
- Auntie Felma!</i>

3
00:00:43,567 --> 00:00:44,900
<i>- Jessica!
- Jessica!</i>

4
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:47,433
<i>Go ahead. You can decide
for yourself.</i>

5
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:48,867
<i> I'm sorry, Mommy.</i>

6
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,267
<i> I'm choosing to stay.</i>

7
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:54,500
<i>You're choosing that home
wrecker over me? Your real mom?</i>

8
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:56,233
<i> Go ahead, then!</i>

9
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:57,733
<i> But I promise you...</i>

10
00:00:57,867 --> 00:00:58,900
<i> I promise you, Felma,</i>

11
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:00,800
<i>this is not over yet!
I will settle this!</i>

12
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:03,400
<i>And I will make sure that I win!</i>

13
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,000
<i> That stubborn child!</i>

14
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:10,500
<i>She chose to stay with Felma...</i>

15
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:12,267
<i>Why don't you bash her
online again?</i>

16
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:14,100
<i>We can contact that
famous vlogger,</i>

17
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:16,333
<i> Karla Talakera.</i>

18
00:01:16,467 --> 00:01:18,300
<i>All right, my fellow
gossipmongers!</i>

19
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:20,633
<i> It's me, Karla Talakera.</i>

20
00:01:20,767 --> 00:01:25,567
<i>Presenting our special guest
for today, Madame C!</i>

21
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:26,600
<i> Thank you, Karla.</i>

22
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:28,700
<i> So, where is your husband now?</i>

23
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:31,733
<i>He's staying with that flirty
Felma.</i>

24
00:01:31,867 --> 00:01:34,667
<i>Sir Manuel! You have to see
this!</i>

25
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:37,033
<i>Imagine, she made my husband
go against me.</i>

26
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:38,867
<i> And now, my own child!</i>

27
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,967
<i>She's making me out to be
the bad mother,</i>

28
00:01:41,133 --> 00:01:42,333
<i> but she's the one who's bad!</i>

29
00:01:42,467 --> 00:01:45,100
<i>Did you know her children
left her?</i>

30
00:01:45,233 --> 00:01:46,667
<i>They couldn't stand
what she was doing!</i>

31
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,400
<i> Hey! What's going on here?</i>

32
00:01:48,533 --> 00:01:49,467
<i> Why?</i>

33
00:01:49,833 --> 00:01:51,567
<i>You better be ready,
Flirty Felma,</i>

34
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:54,400
<i>cause I'm not done with you yet!</i>

35
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:55,900
<i> Felma shouldn't see this.</i>

36
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:57,533
<i> Wait, friends!</i>

37
00:01:57,667 --> 00:01:59,400
<i>Someone's disagreeing with her!</i>

38
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:03,300
<i>She's Felma Ruiz's best friend.</i>

39
00:02:03,433 --> 00:02:05,433
<i> I'll tell you the whole truth.</i>

40
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:07,767
<i>Click this link
before it's blocked.</i>

41
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,333
<i>Before they block it,
wait a minute, friends, please,</i>

42
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:11,933
<i> let's watch this.</i>

43
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:17,033
<i> Hey! Hazel the witch!</i>

44
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:18,667
<i> You'd better stop this!</i>

45
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,167
<i> You're not the victim here.</i>

46
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,800
<i> You're the villain!</i>

47
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:25,500
<i> And you? What are you?</i>

48
00:02:25,633 --> 00:02:27,300
<i> An attack dog?</i>

49
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:28,733
<i> Are you Felma's dog?</i>

50
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,600
<i>Why can't she fight for herself?</i>

51
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,267
<i> Because she's classy.</i>

52
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:35,067
<i>But me? I have no breeding!
So I'll fight you!</i>

53
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,400
<i>Hey, you gossipmongers
and livestream viewers,</i>

54
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:37,800
<i> listen to me!</i>

55
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:40,333
<i> Felma is not a mistress.</i>

56
00:02:40,467 --> 00:02:41,833
<i> She was the first wife!</i>

57
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:42,900
Are you stupid?

58
00:02:43,033 --> 00:02:44,933
They all know he married me!

59
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:46,667
So I'm the legal wife!

60
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,367
<i> Yes, he married you.</i>

61
00:02:49,533 --> 00:02:52,933
But did they know
it was a shotgun wedding?

62
00:02:53,067 --> 00:02:56,333
Hey, guys! Friends!
Ladies and gentlemen.

63
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:59,267
She got Manuel drunk
back in Saudi Arabia.

64
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:02,067
After that,
she got herself pregnant,

65
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:04,433
then threatened him
that she'd report him

66
00:03:04,567 --> 00:03:09,667
to the police
if he didn't marry her!

67
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,000
Shut up!

68
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:12,400
That's not true!

69
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:15,567
Netizens, don't believe that
loser!

70
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:17,667
Oh, really? You're calling me
a loser?

71
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,900
And you? What do you
call yourself?

72
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:21,267
Aren't you mistreating
your husband and daughter?

73
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:22,867
You're abusing them!

74
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,800
So what did they do?

75
00:03:24,933 --> 00:03:26,667
They ran away from you,
didn't they?

76
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,567
They returned to the
Philippines.

77
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,333
And then Felma,

78
00:03:30,467 --> 00:03:33,033
even though she was so mad
at him,

79
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:35,100
still helped them out!

80
00:03:35,233 --> 00:03:36,733
<i> You shameless woman!</i>

81
00:03:36,867 --> 00:03:39,233
<i>My friend is not a home wrecker!</i>

82
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:40,667
That woman is a husband beater

83
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,967
and child abuser! That bitch!

84
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:45,267
So, you're the real villain?

85
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,133
Husband beater.

86
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:49,733
Child abuser.

87
00:03:50,767 --> 00:03:52,000
Hey!

88
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:54,167
Netizens! What's this?

89
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:55,600
So now you're siding with Felma?

90
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:58,133
Really? What gullible fools!
Simple-minded!

91
00:03:58,267 --> 00:03:59,533
Shameless people!

92
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:01,833
You're all so easy to fool!

93
00:04:01,967 --> 00:04:02,867
Go to hell!

94
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Really?

95
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,100
Why did you turn that off?

96
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:08,300
What do I do!

97
00:04:08,433 --> 00:04:09,533
It's gone! I got disconnected!

98
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:11,733
Connect me back! What the heck!

99
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:15,200
Madame, my followers
might turn on me.

100
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:17,000
- I'm done!
- I don't care!

101
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:18,233
Did you see what they wrote?

102
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,133
Jessica.

103
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:26,300
Hazel, can you stop
slandering my wife?

104
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,100
What did you say?

105
00:04:32,067 --> 00:04:33,600
<i> Your wife?</i>

106
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,867
I'm your wife!

107
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,533
No!

108
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:41,033
Only Felma treats me
like a husband.

109
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:43,167
You know how you made me feel?

110
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:44,900
Like I'm your employee!

111
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:47,200
You treat me
as if I work for you!

112
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,433
You really want me
to sue you, don't you?

113
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:51,633
<i> Go ahead, sue me!</i>

114
00:04:51,767 --> 00:04:53,067
But leave Felma out of this.

115
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,667
She has nothing to do with it!

116
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,767
<i> No!</i>

117
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,933
She's an accomplice!

118
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:00,400
She's involved in kidnapping
my daughter!

119
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:03,100
<i>So both of you will go to jail!</i>

120
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:04,567
I won't just destroy her.

121
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,400
I'll put her in jail!

122
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:08,067
Hazel, Hazel, no!

123
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,333
<i> Oh, now you're afraid?</i>

124
00:05:10,467 --> 00:05:12,033
Afraid of what might happen
to your mistress?

125
00:05:13,767 --> 00:05:16,067
If you don't want to go to jail
with that woman...

126
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:20,167
you and Jessica had better
come back to me.

127
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,867
<i> Come back!</i>

128
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,033
Dad, no!

129
00:05:24,167 --> 00:05:26,200
Dad, we can't!

130
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:28,900
<i> I will give you until tonight.</i>

131
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:30,533
I'll wait for you, Manuel.

132
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,433
But I'm warning you...

133
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,967
If you don't come back...

134
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:39,500
I'll see you in court.

135
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:42,900
Wait for your subpoena.

136
00:05:58,167 --> 00:06:01,300
<i>I'm hoping that my husband
and daughter will realize</i>

137
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:03,600
<i>that I'm their family
and not that Felma.</i>

138
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:07,133
<i>So you better be ready,
Flirty Felma,</i>

139
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:09,767
<i>because I'm not done
with you yet!</i>

140
00:06:11,233 --> 00:06:14,100
<i>I swear, I will get
my family back!</i>

141
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:17,467
<i>I'll die before I let you
claim them as yours!</i>

142
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,300
How are we going to stop
that woman?

143
00:06:22,433 --> 00:06:25,000
<i>I'm the legal wife!
I'm the real mother.</i>

144
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:29,433
What's that about?

145
00:06:30,467 --> 00:06:32,167
You don't care about that?

146
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,100
I did care earlier.

147
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:36,333
And then I realized...

148
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:38,333
There's nothing I can do.

149
00:06:38,467 --> 00:06:40,067
She's slandering
our mom, Andrea.

150
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,500
What the heck!

151
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:44,233
Didn't mom treat us unfairly?

152
00:06:44,367 --> 00:06:47,100
She chose her ex over us.

153
00:06:47,233 --> 00:06:49,133
She let us leave.

154
00:06:49,267 --> 00:06:51,433
And now, it looks like
we're the ones who did wrong!

155
00:06:51,567 --> 00:06:53,233
Why should I get involved
in her problem?

156
00:06:53,367 --> 00:06:56,033
She brought it upon herself.

157
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:58,000
Can you forget about
that issue for now?

158
00:06:59,033 --> 00:07:01,033
We should focus
on what Hazel is doing!

159
00:07:03,767 --> 00:07:05,300
Okay, fine.

160
00:07:05,433 --> 00:07:07,333
On the next livestream
of Karla Talakera

161
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:10,400
and Hazel, I'll expose
in the comments

162
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:13,767
everything her husband
did to our family.

163
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,633
To make him feel shame.

164
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,967
What?

165
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:18,667
You're going to put
our life story out there?

166
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,900
It'll only hurt mom more.
Are you going to hurt her?

167
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:23,500
If that's what needs
to be done...

168
00:07:25,367 --> 00:07:27,100
So she'll come to her senses
and finally stay away

169
00:07:27,233 --> 00:07:28,300
from that man.

170
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:31,900
The person who keeps ruining
our lives!

171
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:33,433
Then try it!

172
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:36,433
I'm warning you, Andrea,
you'll have me to answer for!

173
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:38,267
You'll end up losing a brother!

174
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,067
Go on, then.

175
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,967
You, mom, Coleen,

176
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:43,333
and your father can all be
together for all I care!

177
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:59,467
Here...

178
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:00,467
you guys should eat.

179
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:03,300
To relieve our stress.

180
00:08:03,433 --> 00:08:04,300
What?

181
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:06,367
Okay, there.

182
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:07,700
Bring it here.

183
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:09,767
So guys, you know
what to do, right?

184
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:10,967
Yes, Ma'am.

185
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:14,100
Edwina and I will take turns
monitoring our website.

186
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:18,933
We'll see if Karla Talakera and
Hazel go on a livestream again

187
00:08:19,067 --> 00:08:20,300
to slander Ma'am Felma.

188
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:23,767
Good, report it to me
right away, okay?

189
00:08:23,933 --> 00:08:25,933
I'll make some memes
that could go viral.

190
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:29,667
It could be trending, right?

191
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,700
You know...

192
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:31,900
there, I'm gonna make
one right now.

193
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:33,567
I have a lot of ideas...

194
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:36,967
What's going on here?

195
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:41,900
Oh, my!

196
00:08:42,033 --> 00:08:46,200
Don't waste your time
on that woman!

197
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:47,467
Come on, Felma.

198
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,733
That wench shamed you publicly.

199
00:08:49,867 --> 00:08:52,967
Did you think that
we'll just sit here pretty?

200
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,433
We can do something.

201
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,100
I will contact Noah's lawyer.

202
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:58,733
The one who helped us before.

203
00:08:58,867 --> 00:09:00,500
I will contact him.

204
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:04,567
We didn't push through with
the case against Hazel before

205
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,100
because she returned to Canada.

206
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:07,767
But now that she's here,

207
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:09,433
I will see her in court.

208
00:09:09,567 --> 00:09:10,633
There you go!

209
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:13,500
I thought we were just gonna
sit here and do nothing.

210
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,633
Why does it seem like
something's different?

211
00:09:34,967 --> 00:09:38,667
I changed the curtains.

212
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:43,733
I also changed the comforter,
pillowcase, and blanket.

213
00:09:45,667 --> 00:09:47,333
Another welcome gift.

214
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:49,133
No.

215
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:51,600
Joel, I don't like this.

216
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:52,933
Don't get me wrong.

217
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,400
You're my landlord,

218
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:56,667
and I'm your tenant.

219
00:09:57,767 --> 00:10:00,500
I don't want any special favors.

220
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:01,800
I'm not comfortable with that.

221
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:04,667
For all the expenses,

222
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,067
send me a quotation
and I will pay you back.

223
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,633
Andrea, that's not necessary,
come on.

224
00:10:08,767 --> 00:10:10,800
I'm doing all of this

225
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:12,933
especially for my new friends.

226
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,200
Don't give it another meaning.

227
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:29,033
And I also put groceries
in the fridge.

228
00:10:29,167 --> 00:10:31,433
So, you don't have to buy them.

229
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:35,400
And there's food coming
for dinner.

230
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,367
And please...

231
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,167
Please...

232
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,967
don't try to pay me back.

233
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,800
Why?

234
00:10:49,633 --> 00:10:51,333
Nothing.

235
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:52,933
Thank you.

236
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:57,933
Come on.

237
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,100
Hey! Hey!

238
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,133
Are you ready? Up!

239
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:19,067
Two, three, four, chin up!

240
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,600
Six, seven, eight, down.

241
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:29,233
Okay, one more...

242
00:11:30,567 --> 00:11:31,867
Up.

243
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:36,000
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven...

244
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:39,533
Hey, Friend.

245
00:11:39,667 --> 00:11:41,167
What are you doing?
Why did you stop?

246
00:11:42,767 --> 00:11:44,967
No, I can't focus.

247
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,267
Manuel isn't calling me.

248
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:50,067
Didn't he get scared
that I would sue them?

249
00:11:50,533 --> 00:11:52,700
As if you can go through
with it.

250
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:54,767
You can't even afford a lawyer.

251
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:56,800
They didn't know that.

252
00:11:56,933 --> 00:11:58,100
It's between you and me.

253
00:11:58,233 --> 00:11:59,700
I'm just bluffing him.

254
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:02,467
I'm making him think
that I will sue them.

255
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,800
Oh, wait.

256
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,333
What are you going to do?

257
00:12:07,467 --> 00:12:09,633
- I'm gonna call him.
- Don't!

258
00:12:09,767 --> 00:12:11,533
You're going to call him again?

259
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:13,100
Wait for them to call.

260
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,633
Trust me, they will.

261
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,300
Come on.

262
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,933
Hey, wait.

263
00:12:26,933 --> 00:12:28,133
Wait.

264
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:32,967
Yes, Manuel?

265
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:36,233
What? Have you made a decision?

266
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,667
Hazel, we'll come back to you.

267
00:12:41,133 --> 00:12:43,600
But leave Felma out of this.

268
00:12:43,733 --> 00:12:45,500
Of course.

269
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:47,267
I know how to keep my word.

270
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:50,967
So, when are we going to meet?

271
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:53,500
When will I see you and Jessica?

272
00:12:53,633 --> 00:12:55,067
Dad, no, please.

273
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:58,267
Don't agree with what
she wanted!

274
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:01,133
Jessica, I've made up my mind.

275
00:13:01,267 --> 00:13:03,700
She will never leave Felma alone
if we don't go back to her.

276
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:04,867
No!

277
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,400
If you want to go back to her,
then you can go alone!

278
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:08,733
I'm staying here!

279
00:13:08,867 --> 00:13:10,600
Jessica, don't raise
your voice at me!

280
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:13,933
We're going back to your mom
whether you like it or not.

281
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,867
Why don't you answer it?

282
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:29,767
It's nothing important,

283
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:30,533
- my buddy...
- It's been ringing,

284
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:31,767
just answer it.

285
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:33,333
My buddy is just messing around,
but you're more important.

286
00:13:33,467 --> 00:13:35,033
- Go on, it could be important.
- You matter more than this.

287
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:36,600
- Let's go.
- Go there now,

288
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:38,067
It might be important.

289
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,100
- No.
- Go on, I'll be fine here.

290
00:13:40,233 --> 00:13:41,333
But what about the...

291
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:43,500
Go on! Go on!

292
00:13:43,633 --> 00:13:44,700
- Go on.
- You're more important.

293
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:47,833
- You're more important.
- Go on, she might get mad.

294
00:13:47,967 --> 00:13:49,300
- What?
- Go ahead.

295
00:13:49,433 --> 00:13:51,033
- But...
- It could be important.

296
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:52,433
What about your stuff?

297
00:13:52,567 --> 00:13:54,033
- I'm having a hard time now.
- But...

298
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,333
- You'll be okay?
- Go on, I'll be okay.

299
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:56,367
- Yes.
- Are you sure?

300
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,933
- All right.
- Go on!

301
00:13:58,067 --> 00:14:00,333
- Okay, bye, you sure?
- Don't give me a hard time.

302
00:14:00,467 --> 00:14:01,500
Okay.

303
00:14:01,633 --> 00:14:02,500
The...

304
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,633
- Put an ice on it, okay?
- Go on.

305
00:14:04,767 --> 00:14:05,733
- Go.
- Bye.

306
00:14:05,867 --> 00:14:07,367
Okay, okay, okay!

307
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:11,133
Sweetie...

308
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,067
I'm sorry.

309
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:14,400
Stop crying, stop crying.

310
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:15,733
Come on, don't cry.

311
00:14:15,867 --> 00:14:17,433
Manuel...

312
00:14:17,567 --> 00:14:19,433
what's going on?

313
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:21,067
Why are you screaming
at each other?

314
00:14:21,667 --> 00:14:25,367
Dad wants us to go back
to mommy.

315
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:31,067
Felma, we've been causing you
too much trouble.

316
00:14:32,933 --> 00:14:36,133
Because of us,
Jeffrey and Andrea left.

317
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:38,167
And now Hazel's
causing you trouble.

318
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:40,200
I don't want to cause you
any more pain.

319
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:48,500
Don't cry, Jessica.

320
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:51,700
You're not going back
to your mom.

321
00:14:53,133 --> 00:14:54,200
You're staying here.

322
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:57,500
Felma...

323
00:14:57,633 --> 00:14:59,733
Felma, Hazel will never leave
you alone.

324
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,433
She's serious, she's going
to sue you, too!

325
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:10,033
Mom and I were talking
about that earlier, Dad.

326
00:15:10,167 --> 00:15:12,000
She has a plan.

327
00:15:12,133 --> 00:15:14,900
She knows how to make
Hazel stop.

328
00:15:15,033 --> 00:15:18,200
Let's have some dinner for now
and we'll talk about

329
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,667
what we should do.

330
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:24,133
Come on, let's eat.

331
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:51,333
<i>Mom will get hurt,
are you going to hurt her?</i>

332
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:53,067
<i>So she'll come to her senses
and finally stay away</i>

333
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:57,533
<i>from that man, who continuously
ruins our lives!</i>

334
00:15:57,667 --> 00:15:59,233
<i> Okay, just try it!</i>

335
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:01,967
<i>I'm warning you, Andrea,
you'll have me to answer for!</i>

336
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:03,233
<i>You'll end up losing a brother!</i>

337
00:16:03,367 --> 00:16:04,433
<i> Oh, go on then.</i>

338
00:16:04,567 --> 00:16:06,200
<i>You, Mom, Coleen,
and your father</i>

339
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:07,333
<i>can all be together
for all I care!</i>

340
00:16:29,233 --> 00:16:30,933
What are you doing here?

341
00:16:37,167 --> 00:16:38,767
You asked me to help you
move in, remember?

342
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,800
And I also want to check
if you're doing okay here.

343
00:16:43,933 --> 00:16:46,767
I also want to see the man
who helped you out.

344
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:49,800
Of course, I want
to size him up.

345
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,033
He's not here,
he left already.

346
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,200
Aren't we on bad terms
right now?

347
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:58,300
So what?

348
00:17:01,033 --> 00:17:02,467
It doesn't give me a reason
not to check

349
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,733
if you're okay.

350
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:07,600
What's the use of being
a big brother then?

351
00:17:10,233 --> 00:17:11,533
Whatever!

352
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:14,833
You just want to check
if I'm really going to expose

353
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:18,867
your dad when Hazel and that
gossip queen go on live.

354
00:17:24,667 --> 00:17:25,867
You're not gonna do it?

355
00:17:35,067 --> 00:17:36,433
No.

356
00:17:39,133 --> 00:17:41,067
I don't want to lose you.

357
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,200
Is that it?

358
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:53,133
Or you don't want to hurt mom?

359
00:17:58,633 --> 00:17:59,767
Oh, why?

360
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,033
Why do I feel
like this, Jeffrey?

361
00:18:03,267 --> 00:18:05,467
I'm so mad at her,

362
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,033
but I still love her.

363
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:10,633
That's how it is.

364
00:18:11,667 --> 00:18:13,000
We're family.

365
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:15,267
Even though...

366
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,967
we fight like crazy...

367
00:18:20,367 --> 00:18:23,033
we still love each other.

368
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,633
How about you, Jeffrey?
Aren't you mad at mom?

369
00:18:25,767 --> 00:18:27,400
I'm upset.

370
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:29,833
Because she chose...

371
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:32,333
that man over us.

372
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:38,733
You know, Andrea, I'm having
a hard time right now.

373
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:42,033
I can't find a job.

374
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:45,433
And I don't have any savings.

375
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:47,367
I don't want to burden Daisy.

376
00:18:48,633 --> 00:18:53,933
I'm waiting for the virtual
assistant job I applied for.

377
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,067
I'm waiting
for my final interview.

378
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:05,767
Jeffrey, once I get the job,

379
00:19:07,733 --> 00:19:09,767
I will have you get one, too.

380
00:19:11,533 --> 00:19:13,300
I'll be here for you.

381
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:21,000
Thank you.

382
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:27,233
It's just you and me now.

383
00:19:29,133 --> 00:19:31,133
We'll help each other out.

384
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:38,833
Let mom handle her problem
with Hazel.

385
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:42,600
Her ex is with her anyway.

386
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:44,867
They can do whatever they want.

387
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,033
We'll be fine, Jeffrey.

388
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:00,167
Let's eat.

389
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:01,167
What?

390
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:02,467
I'm going to get a plate.

391
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,333
You're going to eat?

392
00:20:06,433 --> 00:20:08,233
Go sit down,
I'll get you a plate.

393
00:20:08,367 --> 00:20:09,467
Sit down.

394
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:10,700
Just let me.

395
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:24,767
Thank you.

396
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:36,367
- Hello?
<i> - Good morning,</i>

397
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:38,600
<i>Miss Hazel Cruz.
This is Franz Tabora</i>

398
00:20:38,733 --> 00:20:40,267
<i>from Southcrest Premier
Hospital's</i>

399
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,867
<i> Human Resources Department.</i>

400
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,433
<i>We'd like to invite you
for an interview</i>

401
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:45,200
<i> next Saturday at 8:00 AM.</i>

402
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:46,700
<i> Would that work for you?</i>

403
00:20:47,767 --> 00:20:49,300
Saturday?

404
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:50,700
<i> Yes, Ma'am.</i>

405
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:53,367
<i>It's at the request
of Miss Miles Andrada.</i>

406
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:54,767
<i>She'd like to see you afterwards</i>

407
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,933
<i>and that's her only available
time next week.</i>

408
00:20:58,433 --> 00:20:59,833
Of course.

409
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:01,100
That would be great.

410
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:02,367
<i> Excellent.</i>

411
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:05,000
<i>Oh, we'll send the details
to your email shortly.</i>

412
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:06,133
Thank you so much.

413
00:21:16,767 --> 00:21:18,600
Manuel...

414
00:21:18,733 --> 00:21:20,433
Why is she here?

415
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:21,800
Where's Jessica?

416
00:21:21,933 --> 00:21:24,267
She will be part
of this discussion.

417
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,533
This is just between you and me.

418
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,967
Why do you have so many people
with you?

419
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,367
Who are these people?

420
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:43,667
Atty. Butch Yeban,
I represent Miss Felma Ruiz

421
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:47,200
in all present and forthcoming
legal matters.

422
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:48,633
And I'm Atty. Aries Tulio,

423
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:51,400
legal counsel
for Mr. Manuel Cruz.

424
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:01,167
Thank you.

425
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:02,300
Thank you so much.

426
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:13,033
Hazel, they're our lawyers.

427
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,033
We are here to advise you
on record

428
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:18,967
that your continued harassment,
defamation,

429
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,833
and online slander
against our clients

430
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:23,500
can and will be met
with full legal action.

431
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:26,933
Stop your false accusations
against Miss Ruiz

432
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:32,800
or she will have to file several
counter complaints against you.

433
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:37,000
On the grounds of trespassing,
cyber libel,

434
00:22:37,133 --> 00:22:41,567
grave oral defamation,
coercion, and assault.

435
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,667
This is based, of course,

436
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:49,200
upon your forced entry
into the house of Miss Ruiz.

437
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:52,767
If you'll file a kidnapping case
against Mr. Cruz and Miss Ruiz,

438
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:54,833
then we'll see you in court.

439
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,067
I was caught off guard, Alice.

440
00:23:03,133 --> 00:23:05,567
Felma and Manuel came...

441
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:08,200
with lawyers.

442
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:09,500
Then suddenly,

443
00:23:09,633 --> 00:23:12,667
they were throwing
all these charges at me.

444
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,533
I looked like a fool there!

445
00:23:14,667 --> 00:23:16,033
I looked so stupid!

446
00:23:17,233 --> 00:23:19,200
Sis, maybe you should let it go.

447
00:23:19,333 --> 00:23:21,100
It's getting to you.

448
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:22,667
Let Manuel go.

449
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:23,933
No!

450
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:27,600
I think you made a mistake
choosing him.

451
00:23:27,733 --> 00:23:30,900
You thought he was the solution
to your problem back then,

452
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:34,333
but he only caused you trouble.

453
00:23:34,467 --> 00:23:36,067
Just take Jessica back.

454
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,667
Manuel is useless anyway.

455
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:39,433
No!

456
00:23:39,567 --> 00:23:41,167
I can't let him go!

457
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:42,833
They're a package!

458
00:23:42,967 --> 00:23:43,967
They're mine!

459
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:46,367
I will get them back!

460
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:49,133
But, Hazel,
you're getting desperate.

461
00:23:50,133 --> 00:23:51,533
Do you love him that much

462
00:23:51,667 --> 00:23:53,667
to do this to yourself?

463
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:55,367
They're mine!

464
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:57,100
They're my family!

465
00:23:57,233 --> 00:23:58,933
They're mine!

466
00:23:59,067 --> 00:24:02,433
My husband, Manuel, is mine!

467
00:24:02,567 --> 00:24:04,367
I'm the only one who should
benefit from him!

468
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:06,167
Just me! No one else!

469
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:07,233
No one else!

470
00:24:07,367 --> 00:24:08,700
- No one else!
- Stop it!

471
00:24:31,433 --> 00:24:33,567
Why is this happening to me?

472
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,667
I just want...

473
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:41,033
I just want to have a family.

474
00:24:42,133 --> 00:24:45,867
When my dad and mom died...

475
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,733
I just want my own family.

476
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:52,300
A family that's mine.

477
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:55,133
Just mine...

478
00:24:55,267 --> 00:24:57,200
a family.

479
00:24:57,333 --> 00:24:59,533
Why is this happening?

480
00:24:59,667 --> 00:25:01,933
Why won't they want me?

481
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:07,800
Was this your 18th birthday
party, Sis?

482
00:25:07,933 --> 00:25:10,833
Yes, but I didn't want
a lavish one.

483
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:12,633
At least you had one.

484
00:25:12,767 --> 00:25:14,867
Your birthday is coming up, too.

485
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:16,300
You're about to have
your 18th debut.

486
00:25:16,433 --> 00:25:18,467
Let's celebrate!

487
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:20,433
Let's do it, Dear.

488
00:25:20,567 --> 00:25:24,067
We can have a small celebration,
that's all we can afford.

489
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,200
I still have a bad feeling
about that woman.

490
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:30,033
Don't even bother thinking about
what drama she's going to pull.

491
00:25:30,167 --> 00:25:34,167
What matters now is that
you focus on Jeff and Andrea.

492
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:37,233
I really hope they come to the
surprise birthday party

493
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:38,267
for Jessica.

494
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,400
I heard something.

495
00:25:40,533 --> 00:25:41,733
Tell me.

496
00:25:41,867 --> 00:25:47,233
Felma's planning to give Jessica
a surprise birthday party.

497
00:25:47,367 --> 00:25:50,433
We never know, your brother and
sister might go to the party.

498
00:25:50,567 --> 00:25:53,900
And we'll get a chance to talk
and make up.

499
00:25:54,033 --> 00:25:57,100
And then we'll all
go home together.

500
00:25:57,233 --> 00:25:59,100
They'll throw a party
for Jessica?

501
00:25:59,233 --> 00:26:00,967
I'll only talk to mom...

502
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:06,700
once that man is out of
our house and out of our lives!

503
00:26:11,433 --> 00:26:15,367
She really wants to take my role
as Jessica's mother.

504
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:16,600
You want a surprise?

505
00:26:16,733 --> 00:26:20,400
Fine, I'll give them a surprise
they'll never forget.
